MBOMBELA &#8211; More than 60 concerned Steiltes residents have signed a petition objecting the proposed rezoning of a portion of former Lowveld Country Club (LVCC) land for a school development. Two more objections were handed in by owners of pre-primary schools located close to the property in question, before the public participation deadline of December 5. GAP Development Planners lodged an application with the City of Mbombela Local Municipality (CMLM) for a property formerly owned by LVCC to be rezoned from &#8220;special&#8221; for sports grounds and purposes related thereto to &#8220;special&#8221; for place or instruction for the purpose of a nursery school, cr che, day-care centre and subservient uses.